WEBVTT


00:00:14.160 --> 00:00:19.999
NO VISITORS ALLOWED

00:00:32.762 --> 00:00:36.474
CLUB WITHDRAWAL FORM

00:00:36.558 --> 00:00:38.852
When we lost our first match at nationals…

00:00:41.104 --> 00:00:43.106
one of the guys cried in the locker room

00:00:43.690 --> 00:00:46.317
and said,
"If only Ryu and Arata were here."

00:00:47.735 --> 00:00:51.739
That was when Seiichi blew up,
which almost never happens.

00:00:53.533 --> 00:00:56.578
He said, "We're the ones
that cornered them."

00:01:05.378 --> 00:01:07.172
Seiichi is right.

00:01:09.174 --> 00:01:10.175
I'm sorry.

00:01:12.552 --> 00:01:13.553
It's fine.

00:01:15.513 --> 00:01:16.973
What will you do after you quit?

00:01:20.768 --> 00:01:22.103
I don't know.

00:01:23.897 --> 00:01:28.902
But I do know something has to change.

00:01:39.662 --> 00:01:40.747
Ryu.

00:01:48.546 --> 00:01:50.131
Don't quit school.

00:01:51.966 --> 00:01:54.594
What's the point in staying
if I'm not playing ice hockey?

00:01:54.677 --> 00:01:55.845
Listen.

00:02:03.394 --> 00:02:05.146
College is where you learn.

00:02:07.023 --> 00:02:08.942
It's where you meet people.

00:02:10.735 --> 00:02:15.240
Ice hockey is only a fraction
of your time here.

00:02:17.575 --> 00:02:18.701
Yeah, but…

00:02:18.785 --> 00:02:20.828
I'll speak to Student Affairs

00:02:21.537 --> 00:02:26.376
so that you won't lose the tuition waiver
from your athletic scholarship.

00:02:34.133 --> 00:02:35.009
Please.

00:02:36.177 --> 00:02:41.015
I don't want to crush the team's future.

00:02:54.445 --> 00:02:55.822
Seiichi.

00:02:59.993 --> 00:03:01.202
Ryu!

00:03:02.203 --> 00:03:04.956
Ryu!

00:03:05.039 --> 00:03:06.165
What the hell?

00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:08.501
-Ryu!
-Hey.

00:03:09.877 --> 00:03:12.338
Well, come on.

00:03:17.719 --> 00:03:19.679
You're seriously quitting?

00:03:21.139 --> 00:03:22.140
Yeah.

00:03:25.435 --> 00:03:28.062
Do you remember
the first time we met in college?

00:03:29.063 --> 00:03:30.064
Yeah.

00:03:30.982 --> 00:03:34.110
"I'm Super Scrappy Seiichi," right?

00:03:34.777 --> 00:03:35.987
No.

00:03:36.863 --> 00:03:39.240
It's, "I'm Super Scrappy Seiichi!"

00:03:39.907 --> 00:03:41.617
There it is. The original version.

00:03:42.869 --> 00:03:46.789
We actually met when we faced off
at the high school nationals.

00:03:46.873 --> 00:03:49.584
But you didn't remember me at all.

00:03:50.543 --> 00:03:52.420
I said I was sorry.

00:03:52.920 --> 00:03:54.464
You should be.

00:03:55.131 --> 00:03:59.677
Well, you and Arata were
a cut above the rest in high school.

00:04:00.178 --> 00:04:04.599
I was thrilled when I found out
we were going to the same college.

00:04:04.682 --> 00:04:07.560
I was determined to become a starter
and play with you.

00:04:09.854 --> 00:04:12.565
Life sure is strange, huh?

00:04:13.816 --> 00:04:16.319
You guys have crazy talent,
yet you're quitting,

00:04:17.570 --> 00:04:20.740
while someone like me is still playing.

00:04:22.075 --> 00:04:25.078
What do you mean, "someone like me"?

00:04:27.663 --> 00:04:31.417
What will you do after leaving the dorm?
Where will you live?

00:04:31.918 --> 00:04:33.044
About that,

00:04:33.544 --> 00:04:37.131
I thought about dropping out
and going back to my hometown.

00:04:37.215 --> 00:04:38.132
Yeah?

00:04:38.216 --> 00:04:40.635
But I'll look for a place tomorrow.

00:04:40.718 --> 00:04:42.595
I haven't told my parents yet though.

00:04:42.678 --> 00:04:43.679
Wait.

00:04:44.430 --> 00:04:45.973
-Hey.
-What?

00:04:46.057 --> 00:04:47.642
Can I come over sometime?

00:04:47.725 --> 00:04:48.726
What?

00:04:50.061 --> 00:04:52.313
Well, sure.

00:04:52.814 --> 00:04:54.982
All right!

00:04:55.775 --> 00:04:59.404
Man, having your own place is the best.

00:04:59.487 --> 00:05:01.697
You can do whatever you want.

00:05:02.490 --> 00:05:07.370
I wanna break out of this dorm
and get a girlfriend.

00:05:07.453 --> 00:05:09.205
The dorm's not the problem.

00:05:09.288 --> 00:05:10.623
It is too!

00:05:11.499 --> 00:05:13.918
I couldn't properly join
the parade last year.

00:05:14.001 --> 00:05:15.837
Join us. You're coming, aren't you?

00:05:15.920 --> 00:05:17.046
Of course.

00:05:17.547 --> 00:05:19.465
See you then. Enjoy your meal.

00:05:24.512 --> 00:05:28.057
I can't believe you're reading manga
while drinking.

00:05:29.559 --> 00:05:31.018
It's my choice.

00:05:31.102 --> 00:05:33.563
Man, you're so not cute.

00:05:33.646 --> 00:05:34.981
Another.

00:05:35.565 --> 00:05:38.776
Instead of drinking here all the time,
go make some friends.

00:05:47.201 --> 00:05:48.411
Huh? What is it?

00:05:48.995 --> 00:05:49.829
Huh?

00:05:50.746 --> 00:05:51.664
You made a friend?

00:05:51.747 --> 00:05:52.832
What?

00:05:53.332 --> 00:05:55.168
-Who is it?
-You're so nosy.

00:05:56.002 --> 00:05:57.837
Come on, tell me!

00:05:57.920 --> 00:06:01.382
Ugh, give me a break.
I'm trying to focus on my manga.

00:06:01.883 --> 00:06:04.886
Don't be like that.
Bring your new friend over next time.

00:06:29.452 --> 00:06:32.079
RYU: I QUIT ICE HOCKEY.
I WON'T DROP OUT OF COLLEGE.

00:06:32.163 --> 00:06:33.748
NOT SURE WHAT TO DO THOUGH.

00:06:37.960 --> 00:06:41.964
JUST BE GLAD YOU GET TO GO TO COLLEGE.

00:06:42.048 --> 00:06:45.760
I'M RETIRING TOMORROW.

00:07:08.324 --> 00:07:10.910
RYU: GOOD LUCK.

00:07:10.993 --> 00:07:12.912
"Good luck"? Is he for real?

00:07:49.156 --> 00:07:51.742
Last one! Push harder!

00:08:01.711 --> 00:08:02.712
Last one!

00:08:17.768 --> 00:08:18.978
It's over.

00:08:27.361 --> 00:08:28.446
That Shim Gicheol…

00:08:30.239 --> 00:08:32.575
He went around tempting other boxers too.

00:08:36.203 --> 00:08:38.539
Someone leaked it.

00:08:39.415 --> 00:08:41.542
The association will be kicking him out.

00:08:45.880 --> 00:08:47.131
I'm sorry.

00:08:51.677 --> 00:08:53.846
What are you sorry for?

00:08:54.764 --> 00:08:56.057
Forget it.

00:09:02.396 --> 00:09:06.942
None of the boxers in Korea
have any money.

00:09:10.279 --> 00:09:12.239
But they still continue to box.

00:09:13.532 --> 00:09:16.202
Who would willingly do
something like that…

00:09:18.371 --> 00:09:20.581
after enduring
this hellish training every day?

00:09:37.431 --> 00:09:38.516
Johan.

00:09:40.351 --> 00:09:46.148
You were a troublemaker
from the moment you got here.

00:09:47.858 --> 00:09:52.571
But that troublemaker's eyes
were brighter…

00:09:55.032 --> 00:09:56.492
than anyone else's.

00:09:59.161 --> 00:10:00.538
Back then…

00:10:04.667 --> 00:10:05.835
and even now.

00:10:19.056 --> 00:10:20.266
Thank you so much…

00:10:23.728 --> 00:10:25.187
for everything.

00:10:34.238 --> 00:10:35.281
All right.

00:10:40.327 --> 00:10:41.245
Last one.

00:10:42.955 --> 00:10:43.789
One more time.

00:10:53.674 --> 00:10:57.511
You will be doing on-site training
at a nursing home,

00:10:57.595 --> 00:11:00.890
which is required
to earn credits for this course.

00:11:00.973 --> 00:11:01.974
Ow!

00:11:03.058 --> 00:11:04.143
As written in the syllabus…

00:11:04.226 --> 00:11:05.227
Hey.

00:11:06.687 --> 00:11:07.772
Is it over?

00:11:07.855 --> 00:11:08.689
Not yet.

00:11:09.815 --> 00:11:10.816
Gross.

00:11:10.900 --> 00:11:12.860
I slept so well.

00:11:15.905 --> 00:11:19.158
Two, two, three. Three, two, three.

00:12:19.385 --> 00:12:21.637
Annyeonghaseyo.

00:12:22.429 --> 00:12:24.932
Huh? Are you drunk?

00:12:26.559 --> 00:12:29.103
I sure am. Got a problem with that?

00:12:30.521 --> 00:12:32.731
You're not good with alcohol.

00:12:33.315 --> 00:12:34.608
Oh, come on.

00:12:38.112 --> 00:12:41.991
So, how was your retirement?
Did you have a ceremony?

00:12:42.074 --> 00:12:43.742
A ceremony?

00:12:45.077 --> 00:12:48.289
Why would I have one?
I wasn't even a champion.

00:12:49.290 --> 00:12:52.751
Just like always, I jogged,

00:12:52.835 --> 00:12:54.795
sparred, and that was it.

00:12:55.296 --> 00:12:56.297
I see.

00:12:58.966 --> 00:13:04.471
I also stayed for drinks with the coach.

00:13:05.347 --> 00:13:06.891
-You did?
-Yeah.

00:13:07.391 --> 00:13:08.934
Good job.

00:13:11.186 --> 00:13:13.063
Show more respect.

00:13:14.315 --> 00:13:16.358
I'm surprised you know
such a difficult word.

00:13:16.442 --> 00:13:18.861
Of course I do.

00:13:19.361 --> 00:13:22.448
"Respect" is fundamental for Koreans.

00:13:24.742 --> 00:13:26.035
Is that so?

00:13:26.911 --> 00:13:28.203
It is.

00:13:31.123 --> 00:13:32.499
It's over.

00:13:34.335 --> 00:13:39.506
Now I can eat as much as I want.
Jjajangmyeon, jjamppong, chicken, pizza.

00:13:41.717 --> 00:13:43.677
Are you happy you quit boxing?

00:13:43.761 --> 00:13:45.804
Yeah, I am.

00:13:46.305 --> 00:13:49.058
Aren't you happy?

00:13:49.558 --> 00:13:53.395
You can do whatever you want
from here on out.

00:13:56.357 --> 00:14:00.361
Don't you ever feel lost?

00:14:00.945 --> 00:14:02.112
Well…

00:14:07.034 --> 00:14:10.079
Getting lost is a good thing.

00:14:14.833 --> 00:14:17.836
I'm starting my military service.

00:14:20.673 --> 00:14:22.341
Huh? For how long?

00:14:23.842 --> 00:14:25.094
About two years.

00:14:26.804 --> 00:14:28.681
Two years?

00:14:31.183 --> 00:14:33.852
Is that short? Or long?

00:14:34.979 --> 00:14:37.606
Jeez, that's long.

00:14:40.359 --> 00:14:43.654
Koreans are obligated to serve.
I have no choice.

00:14:44.530 --> 00:14:48.826
But you Japanese people can use that time

00:14:49.326 --> 00:14:51.328
to wander.

00:14:52.538 --> 00:14:55.833
You can take your time
figuring out what you want to do.

00:14:58.335 --> 00:14:59.753
Isn't that a good thing?

00:15:09.680 --> 00:15:10.931
You think there'll be any?

00:15:11.015 --> 00:15:12.016
Huh?

00:15:14.893 --> 00:15:16.854
You think there'll be any young girls?

00:15:21.692 --> 00:15:23.610
We're almost there. You can do it.

00:15:23.694 --> 00:15:25.487
Come on.

00:15:27.781 --> 00:15:30.034
-I don't wanna anymore.
-What?

00:15:32.202 --> 00:15:33.495
You wanna head back?

00:15:37.374 --> 00:15:39.793
A bit further. That was close!

00:15:39.877 --> 00:15:41.628
-Yes!
-So close.

00:15:42.463 --> 00:15:44.256
-All right. Here!
-Go!

00:15:44.757 --> 00:15:46.925
You got it. Nice!

00:15:49.219 --> 00:15:53.640
Take the top sheet
and align it with the bottom.

00:15:54.600 --> 00:15:55.809
Like this.

00:15:55.893 --> 00:15:57.394
-That's right.
-I'm good.

00:15:57.478 --> 00:15:59.146
-So fast.
-Right?

00:15:59.229 --> 00:16:01.106
-How was that?
-Not bad for your first time.

00:16:01.190 --> 00:16:02.900
-Oh, thank you.
-Thank you.

00:16:02.983 --> 00:16:05.360
Should we do that one next?

00:16:05.444 --> 00:16:06.695
-This one too?
-Yes.

00:16:06.779 --> 00:16:10.407
-Okay.
-I'll go over to the head side.

00:16:12.659 --> 00:16:14.495
Take the top…

00:16:17.748 --> 00:16:18.916
Dammit.

00:16:18.999 --> 00:16:21.710
Man, this is so tough.

00:16:22.252 --> 00:16:23.754
What are we doing here?

00:16:23.837 --> 00:16:25.380
This is exhausting.

00:16:26.381 --> 00:16:28.008
Practice isn't as tiring as this.

00:16:28.926 --> 00:16:32.596
How is pulling weeds
part of our training, anyway?

00:16:32.679 --> 00:16:34.264
What's this gotta do with caregiving?

00:16:34.348 --> 00:16:35.349
Hey.

00:16:36.183 --> 00:16:37.768
Will you focus on your work?

00:16:38.519 --> 00:16:39.895
-Yes, ma'am.
-Yes, ma'am.

00:16:40.395 --> 00:16:42.481
When you're done, carry that over.

00:16:42.564 --> 00:16:43.774
Then, it's bathing time.

00:16:50.280 --> 00:16:51.448
She's a young girl.

00:16:53.951 --> 00:16:55.577
Nah.

00:16:56.203 --> 00:17:00.332
I prefer someone nicer and more ladylike.

00:17:01.500 --> 00:17:03.252
Will you answer me?

00:17:03.919 --> 00:17:05.379
-Yes, ma'am!
-Yes, ma'am!

00:17:09.174 --> 00:17:11.093
This is so much.

00:17:11.176 --> 00:17:12.219
Huh?

00:17:12.302 --> 00:17:17.057
I mean, this isn't what I imagined.

00:17:17.808 --> 00:17:20.060
The job is physically demanding.

00:17:21.353 --> 00:17:22.813
Are you being sarcastic?

00:17:23.814 --> 00:17:25.816
No, that wasn't my intention.

00:17:26.567 --> 00:17:29.236
I can't stand people like you guys.

00:17:29.862 --> 00:17:32.447
-We don't like you either.
-What?

00:17:33.615 --> 00:17:34.783
Oh, sorry.

00:17:34.867 --> 00:17:37.661
This might be
part of your course or whatever,

00:17:37.744 --> 00:17:42.207
but I don't get paid a cent
for babysitting you two.

00:17:42.291 --> 00:17:44.418
Ugh, hey. Not that way.

00:17:44.501 --> 00:17:46.670
It's this way. To the right.

00:17:49.840 --> 00:17:50.924
Are you okay?

00:17:51.425 --> 00:17:52.467
Yeah.

00:17:53.051 --> 00:17:55.888
How is this? Am I scrubbing too hard?

00:17:55.971 --> 00:18:00.350
No. It feels nice.

00:18:00.851 --> 00:18:02.352
Good.

00:18:03.145 --> 00:18:04.855
Do you feel itchy anywhere?

00:18:04.938 --> 00:18:07.274
Oh, that's nice.

00:18:11.445 --> 00:18:13.113
Can you turn the water off?

00:18:13.197 --> 00:18:14.198
Sure.

00:18:14.865 --> 00:18:17.242
All right, let's rinse you off.

00:18:17.326 --> 00:18:19.411
Thank you.

00:18:19.494 --> 00:18:20.579
Here we go.

00:18:22.873 --> 00:18:24.708
Yeah, I'm heading back tomorrow.

00:18:26.001 --> 00:18:28.587
Yeah, I got a ticket from the Busta.

00:18:29.922 --> 00:18:32.549
Huh? No, from the Busta.

00:18:33.967 --> 00:18:37.012
Not pasta. Busta.

00:18:38.347 --> 00:18:41.391
Yeah.

00:18:43.060 --> 00:18:44.645
Sorry, I have to hang up now.

00:18:44.728 --> 00:18:46.813
Yeah. Okay, bye.

00:18:50.567 --> 00:18:52.069
Surprise.

00:18:53.028 --> 00:18:54.029
What?

00:18:56.406 --> 00:18:59.368
Guess where I am right now.

00:19:01.119 --> 00:19:02.371
Where?

00:19:03.121 --> 00:19:05.249
I don't even know where you live in Korea.

00:19:07.417 --> 00:19:09.294
I'm at Narita Airport.

00:19:09.378 --> 00:19:10.379
What?

00:19:10.879 --> 00:19:13.173
Where do you live?

00:19:14.925 --> 00:19:16.051
Seriously?

00:19:43.912 --> 00:19:45.080
Annyeong.

00:19:45.706 --> 00:19:47.457
"Annyeong"?

00:19:47.541 --> 00:19:50.627
This really is a surprise.
You should've told me you were coming.

00:19:50.711 --> 00:19:52.963
Then it wouldn’t have been a surprise.

00:19:53.046 --> 00:19:54.840
Well, that's true, but…

00:19:55.340 --> 00:19:57.467
What? Aren't you happy to see me?

00:19:58.552 --> 00:20:00.053
I guess I am.

00:20:00.137 --> 00:20:01.221
Then it's fine.

00:20:01.847 --> 00:20:05.017
What were you gonna do
if I already had plans?

00:20:11.231 --> 00:20:12.399
Wait, I do.

00:20:13.150 --> 00:20:14.276
What?

00:20:14.359 --> 00:20:15.193
I have plans.

00:20:15.277 --> 00:20:18.405
Well, a friend suddenly came over.

00:20:19.865 --> 00:20:22.993
Uh, it's a guy I met a while back.

00:20:24.703 --> 00:20:27.706
No, he's not from college.

00:20:28.206 --> 00:20:29.333
Yeah.

00:20:29.416 --> 00:20:30.917
He's not Japanese.

00:20:40.886 --> 00:20:41.887
Wow.

00:20:42.929 --> 00:20:44.181
They said it's fine.

00:20:45.640 --> 00:20:47.434
-They did?
-Yeah.

00:20:47.517 --> 00:20:48.518
By the way,

00:20:49.353 --> 00:20:50.979
why are you going home?

00:20:53.357 --> 00:20:54.566
Wait one second.

00:20:56.902 --> 00:20:59.071
Let's see.

00:20:59.154 --> 00:21:00.947
In Korean, it's…

00:21:01.031 --> 00:21:02.032
Yeah?

00:21:02.991 --> 00:21:04.951
-Whoa!
-Huh?

00:21:05.035 --> 00:21:05.994
Sorry, I missed it.

00:21:06.078 --> 00:21:07.245
Dammit.

00:21:07.329 --> 00:21:08.455
Chesa?

00:21:09.122 --> 00:21:10.499
J-Jesa?

00:21:11.917 --> 00:21:12.793
Jesa?

00:21:12.876 --> 00:21:13.960
Yeah.

00:21:16.963 --> 00:21:18.924
Are you sure it's okay?

00:21:19.424 --> 00:21:21.718
Don't start worrying now.

00:21:22.386 --> 00:21:23.387
Um…

00:21:24.554 --> 00:21:30.185
But jesa is an important day for families.

00:21:31.186 --> 00:21:33.939
My parents were actually
kind of happy about this.

00:21:34.564 --> 00:21:35.649
Okay.

00:21:36.149 --> 00:21:37.317
Thanks.

00:21:37.401 --> 00:21:39.653
By the way,
how long are you staying in Japan?

00:21:40.362 --> 00:21:41.530
Two nights.

00:21:43.031 --> 00:21:44.032
I see.

00:21:46.910 --> 00:21:48.161
Are you feeling sad?

00:21:49.996 --> 00:21:52.332
It's just shorter than I thought.

00:21:53.375 --> 00:21:55.127
I need to prepare for the military.

00:21:55.210 --> 00:21:56.336
Yeah.

00:22:01.216 --> 00:22:04.136
Since you're in Tokyo,
is there anywhere you want to go?

00:22:08.181 --> 00:22:09.015
There is.

00:22:16.940 --> 00:22:17.941
Oh!

00:22:18.024 --> 00:22:19.651
Blade of the Immortal.

00:22:21.820 --> 00:22:23.113
So old-school.

00:22:23.196 --> 00:22:24.197
Huh?

00:22:24.739 --> 00:22:25.907
Samurai.

00:22:25.991 --> 00:22:27.409
Samu…

00:22:27.492 --> 00:22:29.327
That's more like a ninja.

00:22:31.371 --> 00:22:33.832
No! It's that one.

00:22:34.833 --> 00:22:36.042
Sorry.

00:22:38.795 --> 00:22:41.214
Don't you have manga cafés in Korea?

00:22:42.966 --> 00:22:45.010
-We do.
-You do?

00:22:45.719 --> 00:22:48.013
-We do.
-Oh, you do have them.

00:22:48.096 --> 00:22:48.930
Yeah.

00:22:49.431 --> 00:22:50.432
Okay.

00:22:51.308 --> 00:22:52.476
Nothing.

00:22:52.559 --> 00:22:53.560
Shh.

00:22:58.690 --> 00:23:00.275
-Is this mackerel?
-Yeah.

00:23:01.234 --> 00:23:02.569
Okay, the mackerel.

00:23:05.530 --> 00:23:06.865
Mm, masitda!

00:23:06.948 --> 00:23:09.493
-Oh, I'm glad.
-Yeah.

00:23:16.374 --> 00:23:18.043
-Yeah, masitda.
-Masitda.

00:23:18.126 --> 00:23:18.960
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

00:23:19.044 --> 00:23:22.506
By the way, how old are you?

00:23:22.589 --> 00:23:24.216
I'm 21.

00:23:24.716 --> 00:23:27.344
I see. Hmm?

00:23:27.427 --> 00:23:28.512
-Then…
-Yeah?

00:23:31.431 --> 00:23:32.641
You…

00:23:34.976 --> 00:23:38.146
will drink like this from now on.

00:23:42.692 --> 00:23:44.903
-I've seen that in Korean dramas.
-Yeah.

00:23:45.695 --> 00:23:47.072
In Korea,

00:23:47.781 --> 00:23:52.619
seniors and juniors drink differently.

00:23:53.370 --> 00:23:55.288
Which way of drinking was that?

00:23:55.372 --> 00:23:56.706
The junior way.

00:23:58.917 --> 00:24:00.335
What year were you born?

00:24:00.418 --> 00:24:01.753
-Huh? Me?
-Yeah.

00:24:02.254 --> 00:24:03.505
I was born in

00:24:04.631 --> 00:24:11.096
19… 95.

00:24:11.179 --> 00:24:13.765
-What? Then we're the same age.
-No.

00:24:13.848 --> 00:24:15.350
-You're 21.
-No.

00:24:16.142 --> 00:24:19.145
I'm considered 22 years old in Korea.

00:24:19.229 --> 00:24:20.772
-What?
-Yes.

00:24:20.855 --> 00:24:24.734
I'm Korean. You're Japanese.

00:24:26.486 --> 00:24:30.699
We count ages differently
depending on what country we're from.

00:24:30.782 --> 00:24:32.242
That's my rule.

00:24:32.867 --> 00:24:35.412
What's with that weird rule?

00:24:35.495 --> 00:24:39.165
That's why I'm gonna drink like this.

00:24:45.547 --> 00:24:47.215
Are Korean apartments like this too?

00:24:47.299 --> 00:24:48.967
-No.
-They're not?

00:24:49.050 --> 00:24:51.052
-They're tall.
-I see.

00:24:54.097 --> 00:24:56.141
-My room's upstairs. Second floor.
-Okay.

00:24:58.560 --> 00:24:59.686
It's nice.

00:25:00.186 --> 00:25:01.813
-Is it?
-Yeah.

00:25:04.899 --> 00:25:06.359
Wow.

00:25:07.068 --> 00:25:09.529
Thanks for having me.

00:25:09.613 --> 00:25:10.655
Come in.

00:25:11.698 --> 00:25:13.199
There we go.

00:25:21.625 --> 00:25:22.626
Whoa.

00:25:27.547 --> 00:25:30.884
KOREAN FOR BEGINNERS

00:25:41.019 --> 00:25:43.355
You can dump your stuff over there.

00:25:44.064 --> 00:25:45.398
Okay.

00:25:46.650 --> 00:25:48.026
Man! What the hell?!

00:26:04.459 --> 00:26:05.960
It doesn't work.

00:26:06.044 --> 00:26:07.045
Yeah.

00:26:08.254 --> 00:26:09.839
The light's dead.

00:26:55.885 --> 00:26:57.470
NISHINASUNO SHIOBARA

00:27:06.104 --> 00:27:07.856
Nasu.

00:27:07.939 --> 00:27:09.274
-Huh?
-We're here.

00:27:09.357 --> 00:27:10.984
-Nasu?
-Yeah.

00:27:25.915 --> 00:27:28.001
-Welcome home.
-I'm back.

00:27:31.254 --> 00:27:33.089
-Here.
-Oh.

00:27:33.173 --> 00:27:35.091
My mom and dad.

00:27:35.925 --> 00:27:38.011
Nice to meet you. I'm Hwang Johan.

00:27:39.345 --> 00:27:41.306
You're so handsome!

00:27:41.389 --> 00:27:43.683
Welcome!

00:27:51.566 --> 00:27:57.363
Today is the 13th anniversary
of my little brother's death.

00:27:59.574 --> 00:28:04.037
My brother was a painter.
He was always painting.

00:28:06.247 --> 00:28:10.919
When Ryu was seven, he suddenly said,
"I want to paint the ocean,"

00:28:12.295 --> 00:28:14.672
and moved to Kyushu.

00:28:16.424 --> 00:28:17.258
You see,

00:28:18.176 --> 00:28:20.011
we don't have an ocean around here.

00:28:23.223 --> 00:28:26.309
I know I shouldn't say this
as his older brother,

00:28:27.769 --> 00:28:29.813
but he was an eccentric guy.

00:28:30.730 --> 00:28:31.981
I guess

00:28:32.982 --> 00:28:35.610
when he was focused on something,

00:28:35.693 --> 00:28:40.782
he would get lost in that world
for a long time.

00:28:41.950 --> 00:28:43.034
And…

00:28:45.453 --> 00:28:47.789
he died because of the ocean.

00:29:03.054 --> 00:29:04.430
There we go.

00:29:18.403 --> 00:29:20.572
Oh, right.

00:29:20.655 --> 00:29:27.662
There's a house nearby
that my brother used as an art studio.

00:29:30.498 --> 00:29:33.626
Maybe you could show it to Johan
if he'd like that.

00:29:34.252 --> 00:29:35.670
-Right?
-Yeah.

00:29:35.753 --> 00:29:38.923
Your uncle would be thrilled. Right?

00:29:39.007 --> 00:29:40.008
How about it?

00:29:42.051 --> 00:29:43.094
I'd love to.

00:29:45.221 --> 00:29:47.515
-I'll drive them there.
-Okay.

00:29:48.349 --> 00:29:49.559
Right. Let's clean up.

00:29:55.398 --> 00:29:56.858
Have a safe drive back.

00:30:04.991 --> 00:30:07.452
-All right. Wanna go in?
-Okay.

00:30:15.001 --> 00:30:17.378
You keep the key in a place like that?

00:30:18.254 --> 00:30:20.381
That's how it is
in the countryside in Japan.

00:30:22.342 --> 00:30:23.551
How peaceful.

00:30:24.969 --> 00:30:26.638
-Come in.
-Okay.

00:30:37.315 --> 00:30:39.192
This is the art studio.

00:30:39.275 --> 00:30:40.276
I see.

00:31:27.365 --> 00:31:31.619
My uncle was working on this painting
until the very end.

00:31:41.546 --> 00:31:42.839
This painting…

00:31:46.592 --> 00:31:47.844
feels sad.

00:31:54.642 --> 00:31:55.893
Where is this?

00:32:00.565 --> 00:32:01.858
I wonder.

00:32:04.652 --> 00:32:06.279
But I think…

00:32:08.656 --> 00:32:11.909
he painted it while thinking
of someone special to him.

00:32:19.500 --> 00:32:20.585
I see.

00:32:27.300 --> 00:32:28.426
Hey, Ryu.

00:32:29.427 --> 00:32:31.262
What do you think loneliness is?

00:32:34.724 --> 00:32:37.518
Always being by yourself

00:32:38.019 --> 00:32:40.855
without any friends.

00:32:41.689 --> 00:32:42.607
Being alone!

00:32:46.486 --> 00:32:48.780
Is that how you see me?

00:32:49.280 --> 00:32:53.034
Well, if you move far away,
we can't see each other, right?

00:32:58.664 --> 00:33:00.708
Well, then. Okay.

00:33:01.501 --> 00:33:03.753
Ryu, come over here.

00:33:03.836 --> 00:33:06.798
Yeah. Now, up you go.

00:33:06.881 --> 00:33:09.467
I've got paint all over my hands.

00:33:10.635 --> 00:33:12.386
I'm a zombie!

00:33:16.599 --> 00:33:17.975
-It's a lot, isn't it?
-Yeah.

00:33:18.059 --> 00:33:19.060
Right?

00:33:25.399 --> 00:33:27.026
You know, loneliness is…

00:33:30.571 --> 00:33:32.198
Loneliness is

00:33:33.699 --> 00:33:38.996
probably the feeling of not having
anyone you truly care about.

00:33:39.497 --> 00:33:41.207
-Hmm?
-Well…

00:33:41.958 --> 00:33:45.795
I've got a lot of people
that I care about.

00:33:47.004 --> 00:33:52.093
When you feel lonely,
try looking at the scenery somewhere.

00:33:52.176 --> 00:33:54.220
It doesn't matter where.

00:33:55.304 --> 00:33:57.181
The scenery?

00:33:57.265 --> 00:33:58.641
Yes, that's right.

00:34:01.060 --> 00:34:02.228
The scenery…

00:34:04.355 --> 00:34:05.773
mirrors your heart.

00:34:06.816 --> 00:34:10.778
If you look at it for a while
and think, "It's pretty,"

00:34:10.862 --> 00:34:13.114
or "It brings back memories,"

00:34:13.197 --> 00:34:18.369
that's because you once saw that scenery
with someone you treasured.

00:34:18.870 --> 00:34:24.208
And you can find
that treasured person in any scenery.

00:34:24.834 --> 00:34:26.043
Do you get why?

00:34:27.170 --> 00:34:29.755
Because the scenery mirrors your heart.

00:34:31.257 --> 00:34:32.633
Do you really get it?

00:34:32.717 --> 00:34:34.719
-I get it.
-Do you?

00:34:34.802 --> 00:34:38.556
-Then do you see anyone in this scenery?
-No.

00:34:38.639 --> 00:34:39.974
What about that one?

00:34:40.474 --> 00:34:41.475
No.

00:34:43.102 --> 00:34:45.479
But one day, you might find someone there.

00:34:45.980 --> 00:34:46.981
Okay?

00:37:36.650 --> 00:37:39.570
Subtitle translation by: Remi Miura